         <abstract id="aspace_79e788cbebe8f381e64b6950464340ed">Gloria Robinson (1924-2017) was a painter and medical illustrator. After completing a PhD in History of Science and Medicine from the Yale School of Medicine in 1969 she was a research affiliate and lecturer in the Yale History of Medicine Department and author of <title>
               <part>A Prelude to Genetics: Theories of a Material Substance of Heredity From Darwin to Weissman</part>
            </title>. The collection contains notes, papers, and syllabi from the History of Medicine course she attended in 1963-1964 while working on her Phd at Yale.</abstract>
